Your boss's Thinking Machine realizes that it can do the job you were told to do because your Thinking Machine could do it.
The company downsizes massively and your role is deemed redundant.
Eventually, this line of thinking drives the company to downsize all of its employees—and the Thinking Machines that are dependent on their owners to physically enact their thoughts.
